    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice (no need to peel!) your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-thigh-and-chickpea-tagine-with-coriander-couscous/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced</strong> <strong>carrot </strong>and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-thigh-and-chickpea-tagine-with-coriander-couscous/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-thigh-and-chickpea-tagine-with-coriander-couscous/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[255ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-thigh-and-chickpea-tagine-with-coriander-couscous/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add your<strong> diced chicken </strong>to the pan and cook for an initial 3-4 min or until lightly browned</p><p>Once lightly browned, add your <strong>ras el hanout</strong> and <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-thigh-and-chickpea-tagine-with-coriander-couscous/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>chickpeas</strong> to the pan with your<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chicken stock</strong>, and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat then reduce to medium-high and cook for 6-8 min or until your sauce has thickened and your chicken has cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken & chickpea tagine</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-thigh-and-chickpea-tagine-with-coriander-couscous/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While your tagine is cooking, add your <strong>couscous</strong> and <strong>remaining chicken stock mix </strong>to a heatproof bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover and set aside until all of the liquid has been absorbed</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Once the liquid has been absorbed, add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to your <strong>couscous </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> coriander couscous</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-thigh-and-chickpea-tagine-with-coriander-couscous/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chicken & chickpea tagine </strong>with the <strong>coriander couscous </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over your<strong> natural yoghurt</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
